---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Us - Health Calculators & Insights | BMICalc"
  description="Learn more about BMICalc, our mission, and the scientific health formulas we use to calculate BMI, BMR, TDEE, and daily caloric needs."
  keywords="about us, health tools, BMI calculators, science formulas, metabolic rate, health tracking"
  canonicalUrl="https://calbmi.com/about.html"
>
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="container" style="padding-top: 3.5rem; padding-bottom: 5rem;">
    <div class="section-header scroll-reveal">
      <div class="section-badge">About Us</div>
      <h1 class="section-title-lg">Empowering Healthier Lifestyles</h1>
      <p class="section-description" style="max-width: 650px; margin: 0.5rem auto 0;">
        BMICalc is dedicated to providing premium, scientific, and highly accurate calculators to help you track your body metrics and daily nutritional goals with absolute clarity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article layout -->
    <div class="card scroll-reveal" style="padding: 2.5rem; max-width: 820px; margin: 2rem auto 0;">
      <div class="seo-article-main" style="margin: 0;">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>At BMICalc, we believe that health metrics should be easily accessible, simple to understand, and completely free. We design interactive, premium utility tools based on established medical formulas to help you analyze your Body Mass Index (BMI), Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR), and Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) with confidence.</p>
        
        <h3>Scientific Integrity First</h3>
        <p>Our application isn't built on placeholders or generic estimates. We implement standard, verified medical formulas used by the World Health Organization (WHO), Center for Disease Control (CDC), and registered clinical dietitians globally:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Body Mass Index (BMI):</strong> Formulated via <code>kg/m²</code> (or the imperial scaled equivalent) to check body weight category boundaries accurately.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal Body Weight (IBW):</strong> Derived using the <strong>Devine Formula</strong>, factoring in biological gender tallies for bone and skeletal structures.</li>
          <li><strong>Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR):</strong> Calculated using the <strong>Mifflin-St Jeor Equation</strong>, recognized by nutritional sciences as the gold standard for metabolic rate estimation.</li>
          <li><strong>Active Calories (TDEE):</strong> Factored using active multipliers spanning five precise physical exertion categories.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Our Team &amp; Philosophy</h3>
        <p>We are a dedicated group of developers, designer enthusiasts, and health researchers who value user experience above all else. We designed BMICalc with a sleek glassmorphic aesthetics, full dark mode capabilities, responsive layouts, and cross-page memory sharing to keep your fitness data connected without needing sign-ups or compromising your privacy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
